35:10.795 --> 35:23.938
and stayed with the place, I would go down to my 
house, because that's where we came from. That's

35:23.958 --> 35:26.282
where they lived since they got married? Yes, 
that's where they worked. He was a horse herder, a

35:29.588 --> 35:36.297
horse herder of animals, he did all the work there. 
He

35:36.317 --> 35:43.487
would be stronger, I don't know. My father liked a 
lot to tie the horses or whatever, and to knock them

35:43.807 --> 35:51.417
down. He wasn't afraid of the animals. He had a lot 
of courage for that. Yes. He really liked to eat

36:00.413 --> 36:04.939
manganese and manzanas and everything. He really 
liked the tobacco. And does he want to leave

36:06.141 --> 36:14.091
the farm? In those days, his mom and dad went to 
Texas. Does his husband really want to go to Texas

36:17.795 --> 36:23.242
too? To go to Texas too? Well, they don't exist 
anymore. They all died. They don't exist anymore.

36:35.039 --> 36:41.345
But they never went, they never went to the west, to 
Mexico. No, they don't want to go. They never

36:45.710 --> 36:47.051
wanted to go. They wanted to go, but they didn't. I 
don't know. I still go because my husband never

36:54.149 --> 37:01.398
said, let's go to Mexico.

37:03.882 --> 37:12.012
And I, a very poor person, told him, let's gather 
money little by little and let's go to Mexico.

37:12.673 --> 37:14.736
Because he had all his people in Monterrey. No, no. 
